----------------------------------------------------------------------
man youtube-dl
----------------------------------------------------------------------
     --audio-quality QUALITY
              Specify ffmpeg/avconv audio quality, insert a value between 0 (better) and 9 (worse) for VBR or a specific bitrate
              like 128K (default 5)


How do I put downloads into a specific folder?
       Use  the -o to specify an output template, for example -o "/home/user/videos/%(title)s-%(id)s.%(ext)s".  If you want this
       for all of your downloads, put the option into your configuration file.


